CatDescriptText: W. Daniels, bus driver, 304 Wood Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the steel strike will be resumed after the 80-day 'cooling-off' period imposed by the Supreme Court under the injection of the Taft-Hartley Act?" answer reads: "I think so. And it would be bad if there is not a settlement."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of W. Daniels wearing dark zippered jacket, dark polo shirt, and eyeglasses, holding wrapped packages, standing in front of sign
